            <div class="col-sm-12 MRSSection status_current">
              <h3 class="heading_section">
                    §5111. Imposition and rate of tax</h3>
              <div class="mrs-text indpara MRSIndentedPara status_current IP">A tax is imposed for each taxable year beginning on or after January 1, 2000, on the Maine taxable income of every resident individual of this State.  The amount of the tax is determined as provided in this section.
                                     
                                <span class="bhistory">[PL 1999, c. 731, Pt. T, §1 (AMD).]</span></div>
              <div class="MRSSubSection">
                <div class="mrs-text indpara">
                  <span class="headnote">1. 
                                Single individuals and married persons filing separate returns. 
                                </span>
                </div>
                <span class="bhistory">[PL 1991, c. 824, Pt. A, §76 (AMD); PL 1991, c. 824, Pt. A, §79 (AFF); MRSA T. 36 §5111, sub-§1 (RP).]</span>
              </div>
              <div class="MRSSubSection">
                <div class="mrs-text indpara">
                  <span class="headnote">1-A. 
                                Single individuals and married persons filing separate returns; tax years beginning 2000, 2001. 
                                </span>For tax years beginning in 2000 or 2001, for single individuals and married persons filing separate returns:<table style=""><colgroup><col style="width:3.06in;" /><col style="width:3.19in;" /></colgroup><tbody style=""><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">If Maine taxable income is:</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">The tax is:</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">Less than $4,150</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">2% of the Maine taxable income</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">At least $4,150 but less than $8,250</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$83 plus 4.5% of the excess over $4,150</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">At least $8,250 but less than $16,500</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$268 plus 7% of the excess over $8,250</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$16,500 or more</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$846 plus 8.5% of the excess over $16,500</span></td></tr></tbody></table></div>
                <span class="bhistory">[PL 1999, c. 731, Pt. T, §2 (RPR).]</span>
              </div>
              <div class="MRSSubSection">
                <div class="mrs-text indpara">
                  <span class="headnote">1-B. 
                                Single individuals and married persons filing separate returns; tax years from 2002 to 2012. 
                                </span>For tax years beginning on or after January 1, 2002 but not later than December 31, 2012, for single individuals and married persons filing separate returns:<table style=""><colgroup><col style="width:3.03in;" /><col style="width:3.19in;" /></colgroup><tbody style=""><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">If Maine Taxable income is:</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">The tax is:</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">Less than $4,200</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">2% of the Maine taxable income</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">At least $4,200 but less than $8,350</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$84 plus 4.5% of the excess over $4,200</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">At least $8,350 but less than $16,700</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$271 plus 7% of the excess over $8,350</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$16,700 or more</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$856 plus 8.5% of the excess over $16,700</span></td></tr></tbody></table></div>
                <span class="bhistory">[PL 2011, c. 380, Pt. N, §1 (AMD); PL 2011, c. 380, Pt. N, §19 (AFF).]</span>
              </div>
              <div class="MRSSubSection">
                <div class="mrs-text indpara">
                  <span class="headnote">1-C. 
                                Single individuals and married persons filing separate returns; tax year 2013. 
                                </span>For tax years beginning on or after January 1, 2013 but not later than December 31, 2013, for single individuals and married persons filing separate returns:<table style=""><colgroup><col style="width:3.19in;" /><col style="width:3.06in;" /></colgroup><tbody style=""><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">If Maine Taxable income is:</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">The tax is:</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">At least $5,000 but less than $19,950</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">6.5% of the excess over $5,000</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$19,950 or more</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$972 plus 7.95% of the excess over $19,950</span></td></tr></tbody></table></div>
                <span class="bhistory">[PL 2013, c. 368, Pt. Q, §3 (AMD).]</span>
              </div>
              <div class="MRSSubSection">
                <div class="mrs-text indpara">
                  <span class="headnote">1-D. 
                                Single individuals and married persons filing separate returns; tax years beginning 2014 and 2015. 
                                </span>For tax years beginning in 2014 or 2015, for single individuals and married persons filing separate returns:<table style=""><colgroup><col style="width:3.06in;" /><col style="width:3.19in;" /></colgroup><tbody style=""><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">If Maine Taxable income is:</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">The tax is:</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">At least $5,200 but less than $20,900</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">6.5% of the excess over $5,200</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$20,900 or more</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$1,021 plus 7.95% of the excess over $20,900</span></td></tr></tbody></table></div>
                <span class="bhistory">[PL 2015, c. 267, Pt. DD, §2 (AMD).]</span>
              </div>
              <div class="MRSSubSection">
                <div class="mrs-text indpara">
                  <span class="headnote">1-E. 
                                Single individuals and married persons filing separate returns; tax years beginning 2016. 
                                </span>For tax years beginning in 2016, for single individuals and married persons filing separate returns:<table style=""><colgroup><col style="width:3.06in;" /><col style="width:3.19in;" /></colgroup><tbody style=""><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">If Maine taxable income is:</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">The tax is:</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">Less than $21,050</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">5.8% of the Maine taxable income</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">At least $21,050 but less than $37,500</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$1,221 plus 6.75% of the excess over $21,050</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$37,500 or more</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$2,331 plus 7.15% of the excess over $37,500</span></td></tr></tbody></table></div>
                <span class="bhistory">[PL 2015, c. 267, Pt. DD, §3 (NEW).]</span>
              </div>
              <div class="MRSSubSection">
                <div class="mrs-text indpara">
                  <span class="headnote">1-F. 
                                Single individuals and married persons filing separate returns; tax years beginning 2017. 
                                </span>For tax years beginning on or after January 1, 2017, for single individuals and married persons filing separate returns:<table style=""><colgroup><col style="width:3.19in;" /><col style="width:3.06in;" /></colgroup><tbody style=""><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">If Maine taxable income is:</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">The tax is:</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">Less than $21,050</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">5.8% of the Maine taxable income</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">At least $21,050 but less than $50,000</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$1,221 plus 6.75% of the excess over $21,050</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$50,000 or more</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$3,175 plus 7.15% of the excess over $50,000</span></td></tr></tbody></table></div>
                <span class="bhistory">[PL 2015, c. 267, Pt. DD, §3 (NEW).]</span>
              </div>
              <div class="MRSSubSection">
                <div class="mrs-text indpara">
                  <span class="headnote">2. 
                                Heads of households. 
                                </span>
                </div>
                <span class="bhistory">[PL 1991, c. 824, Pt. A, §77 (AMD); PL 1991, c. 824, Pt. A, §79 (AFF); MRSA T. 36 §5111, sub-§2 (RP).]</span>
              </div>
              <div class="MRSSubSection">
                <div class="mrs-text indpara">
                  <span class="headnote">2-A. 
                                Heads of households; tax years beginning 2000, 2001. 
                                </span>For tax years beginning in 2000 or 2001, for unmarried individuals or legally separated individuals who qualify as heads of households:<table style=""><colgroup><col style="width:3.06in;" /><col style="width:3.19in;" /></colgroup><tbody style=""><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">If Maine taxable income is:</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">The tax is:</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">Less than $6,200</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">2% of the Maine taxable income</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">At least $6,200 but less than $12,400</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$124 plus 4.5% of the excess over $6,200</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">At least $12,400 but less than $24,750</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$403 plus 7% of the excess over $12,400</span></td></tr><tr style="vertical-align:top;"><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$24,750 or more</span></td><td class="table_cell" colspan="1" style="&#xA;                        text-align: Left;&#xA;                    &#xA;                text-indent: 0px;&#xA;            "><span style="text-align:Left;">$1,268 plus 8.5% of the excess over $24,750</span></td></tr></tbody></table></div>
                <span class="bhistory">[PL 1999, c. 731, Pt. T, §4 (RPR).]</span>
              </div>
              <div class="MRSSubSection">
                <div class="mrs-text indpara">
